<div id="review_533965513" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/533965513" />
    <a title="Michael Carlson" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/5106387-michael-carlson"><img alt="Michael Carlson" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1343903797p2/5106387.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/533965513?book_show_action=true">Feb 12, 2013</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Michael Carlson" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Michael Carlson" href="/user/show/5106387-michael-carlson">Michael Carlson</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer533965513" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11561261721373480361">Sad to say but this is the final book in the Cadfael series by Ellis Peters. I&apos;ve enjoyed every single one of them. My worry in this one was whether the series would end with the now-65-year-old Cadfael dying! The plot suggested it could well have been a possibility! Cadfael offers himself as ransom to release his son (whom he had only recent discovered having in his days before the cloister!).<br/>Without giving any more away, this novel is wonderful, a fitting conclusion to a great series.</span>
  <span id="freeText11561261721373480361" style="display:none">Sad to say but this is the final book in the Cadfael series by Ellis Peters. I've enjoyed every single one of them. My worry in this one was whether the series would end with the now-65-year-old Cadfael dying! The plot suggested it could well have been a possibility! Cadfael offers himself as ransom to release his son (whom he had only recent discovered having in his days before the cloister!).<br />Without giving any more away, this novel is wonderful, a fitting conclusion to a great series.</span>
  <a data-text-id="11561261721373480361" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
