    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_2449720953" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2449720953" />
    <a title="Rob" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1257559-rob"><img alt="Rob" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1214065897p2/1257559.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2449720953?book_show_action=true">Dec 22, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Rob" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Rob" href="/user/show/1257559-rob">Rob</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/40717597-brother-cadfael-s-penance">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1257559-rob?shelf=historical-fiction">historical-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1257559-rob?shelf=medieval">medieval</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2449720953" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3438091904469106473">As the final book in a solid medieval mystery series, it does a good job to include past events and closes with a nice wrap on Cadfael&apos;s devotion and family ties. He struggles between faith and fatherhood, but ultimately everything works itself out. While a nice cap to the series, I felt the book on its own was average with respect to all the others. The actual mystery ran in the background and Ellis Peters placed the character&apos;s internal struggles front and center. Too much emotion and flowery </span>
  <span id="freeText3438091904469106473" style="display:none">As the final book in a solid medieval mystery series, it does a good job to include past events and closes with a nice wrap on Cadfael's devotion and family ties. He struggles between faith and fatherhood, but ultimately everything works itself out. While a nice cap to the series, I felt the book on its own was average with respect to all the others. The actual mystery ran in the background and Ellis Peters placed the character's internal struggles front and center. Too much emotion and flowery language. Not enough mystery, second guessing, and intrigue. Good series though and obviously if you have invested in the first 19.... gotta read this one.</span>
  <a data-text-id="3438091904469106473" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

