<div id="review_3437610570" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3437610570" />
    <a title="J. Lee Hazlett" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/58702014-j-lee-hazlett"><img alt="J. Lee Hazlett" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/u_50x66-632230dc9882b4352d753eedf9396530.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3437610570?book_show_action=true">Jul 18, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="J. Lee Hazlett" class="user" itemprop="url" name="J. Lee Hazlett" href="/user/show/58702014-j-lee-hazlett">J. Lee Hazlett</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/40717597-brother-cadfael-s-penance">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/58702014-j-lee-hazlett?shelf=medieval">medieval</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/58702014-j-lee-hazlett?shelf=historical-fiction">historical-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/58702014-j-lee-hazlett?shelf=mystery">mystery</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/58702014-j-lee-hazlett?shelf=england">england</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3437610570" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13693668276640097631">This book was the perfect ending to the fabulous Cadfael series. I went into it thinking that the author hadn&apos;t known this would be the last tale, and that it would be much like its predecessors as a result. While all the best parts of the earlier Cadfael stories are present, Peters clearly knew she was capping off the series, and this final act is the best one of them all. Everything I didn&apos;t know I wanted to happen actually happened, and although the murder mystery is more of a first subplot t</span>
  <span id="freeText13693668276640097631" style="display:none">This book was the perfect ending to the fabulous Cadfael series. I went into it thinking that the author hadn't known this would be the last tale, and that it would be much like its predecessors as a result. While all the best parts of the earlier Cadfael stories are present, Peters clearly knew she was capping off the series, and this final act is the best one of them all. Everything I didn't know I wanted to happen actually happened, and although the murder mystery is more of a first subplot than the main storyline, that is perfectly okay. It's rare that an author can leave the reader feeling truly sated at the end of a long and much-loved series, but Peters has managed it here.</span>
  <a data-text-id="13693668276640097631" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

<tr class="no_border feedFooterReview" id="update_comment_stuff_Review3437610570">
