<span id="freeTextContainer13792542756080583604">I have just finished reading &quot;Brother Cadfael&apos;s Penance&quot;, the 20th Chronicle of the Welsh monk from Shrewsbury. Sadly there shall be no 21st Chronicle. <br/><br/>There was a special note at the beginning of &quot;Penance&quot; that explained that as the book was going to press the author, Edith Pargeter (Ellis Peters), had passed away.<br/><br/>I had come late to these Medieval mysteries. Though the first book had been published in 1977, I hadn&apos;t discovered Cadfael until the early 1990s. I would pick up a copy here and one t</span>
  <span id="freeText13792542756080583604" style="display:none">I have just finished reading "Brother Cadfael's Penance", the 20th Chronicle of the Welsh monk from Shrewsbury. Sadly there shall be no 21st Chronicle. <br /><br />There was a special note at the beginning of "Penance" that explained that as the book was going to press the author, Edith Pargeter (Ellis Peters), had passed away.<br /><br />I had come late to these Medieval mysteries. Though the first book had been published in 1977, I hadn't discovered Cadfael until the early 1990s. I would pick up a copy here and one there but for about 10 years I lost track of the books. Only recently did I buy the final four books to complete the series.<br /><br />I had found the stories very entertaining, combining a good mystery with good history. I was fascinated by Peters attention of Cadfael's world. "Penance" was especially so. As a history major I was delighted to learn Peters had thoroughly researched the life and times of 12th century England. <br /><br />As I neared the end I found it hard to put the book down. On the other hand, I didn't want the story to end. Like a special song at a concert, you want it to go on and on. <br /><br />I knew that once I reached that final page, there would be no more Cadfael stories. No 21st Chronicle.<br /><br />Thank you Edith for providing me with hours of good reads.<br /><br /><br /><br /><br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="13792542756080583604" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
