<div id="review_3650023904" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3650023904" />
    <a title="giveusaclue" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/70358975-giveusaclue"><img alt="giveusaclue" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1604610814p2/70358975.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3650023904?book_show_action=true">Nov 22, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="giveusaclue" class="user" itemprop="url" name="giveusaclue" href="/user/show/70358975-giveusaclue">giveusaclue</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Mass Market Paperback 9780751513707" href="/book/show/915047.Brother_Cadfael_s_Penance">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3650023904" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6526464530738259633">I finished reading<i> Brother Cadfael’s</i> Penance today and thoroughly enjoyed it.<br/><br/>SPOILER ALERT<br/><br/>In a previous book Cadfael found he had a son, Olivier from a relationship with a Syrian women, who he did not know about until said son was grown. They met when Olivier was escorting two children Yves and his sister to safety in England. Fast forward a few years and Yves rushes to Shrewsbury to say that Olivier had been captured following the fall by deception of Faringdon Castle to Stephen’s side in the w</span>
  <span id="freeText6526464530738259633" style="display:none">I finished reading<i> Brother Cadfael’s</i> Penance today and thoroughly enjoyed it.<br /><br />SPOILER ALERT<br /><br />In a previous book Cadfael found he had a son, Olivier from a relationship with a Syrian women, who he did not know about until said son was grown. They met when Olivier was escorting two children Yves and his sister to safety in England. Fast forward a few years and Yves rushes to Shrewsbury to say that Olivier had been captured following the fall by deception of Faringdon Castle to Stephen’s side in the wars between Stephen and Mathilda, and his wherabouts are not known. It is a story of the changing sides and divisions and reconciliation between family members. The story, and Cadfael, move to Coventry and to Musardie a castle in Gloucestershire, where the descriptions of siege warfare are very well described.<br /><br />The book carries along at a good pace, the frustrations of clergy trying to negotiate a peace between entrenched factions, the strength of brotherhood and honour. It was Peters’ last Cadfael book and I am very glad I found it after all these years.</span>
  <a data-text-id="6526464530738259633" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


