    <a title="Sue" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/3830946-sue"><img alt="Sue" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1350426069p2/3830946.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/413068104?book_show_action=true">Sep 12, 2012</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Sue" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Sue" href="/user/show/3830946-sue">Sue</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3830946-sue?shelf=mystery">mystery</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3830946-sue?shelf=england">england</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3830946-sue?shelf=medieval">medieval</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer413068104" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14590284752679540417"> In the on-going feud between King Stephen and Empress Maud, the castle at Faringdon changed hands to Stephen&apos;s forces. Most of the men taken captive were offered for ransom, but there were a few whose whereabouts were unknown. Among them, Olivier de Bretagne, Cadfael&apos;s son. Hugh brings him the news. A joint council is to be convened in a neutral site for the purpose of seeking a peaceful resolution to the on-going conflicts. Cadfael requests, and is granted, permission to leave the Abbey in ord</span>
  <span id="freeText14590284752679540417" style="display:none"> In the on-going feud between King Stephen and Empress Maud, the castle at Faringdon changed hands to Stephen's forces. Most of the men taken captive were offered for ransom, but there were a few whose whereabouts were unknown. Among them, Olivier de Bretagne, Cadfael's son. Hugh brings him the news. A joint council is to be convened in a neutral site for the purpose of seeking a peaceful resolution to the on-going conflicts. Cadfael requests, and is granted, permission to leave the Abbey in order to attend and seek word on Olivier. Instead of returning at its conclusion, Cadfael is AWOL - a breaking of his vows - in order to continue to seek and attempt to rescue his son.<br /> I don't know if this was intended to be the conclusion of the series, or is so by reason of Peters' death. Either way, it is a fitting conclusion to what has been a very enjoyable series. </span>
  <a data-text-id="14590284752679540417" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


